attachments.title: THUMP // Matt Lange ON DECK by Matt Lange
attachments.text:
Although Los Angeles-based producer Matt Lange has been developing his own take on dark, driving, futurist house and techno for a half-decade now, the buzz around him kicked into overdrive after Mau5trap boss Deadmau5 publicly lauded his new material on Twitter and agreed to put out Lange's stellar album Ephemera, released this September. 

Now, THUMP has Matt Lange ON DECK, and the 50-minute selection is quite the dark journey. Bookended by Lange originals, the mix cheats a penchant for Drumcode with tracks by Sasha Carassi and Nicole Moudaber alongside tunes from Scuba and Oxia.

attachments.title: CLAPTONE RINSE FM OCTOBER TAKEOVER by Claptone
attachments.text:
EVERY FRIDAY IN OCTOBER 21:00-23:00GMT - 106.8FM LDN / <http://Rinse.fm/Player|Rinse.fm/Player>

London based tastemaker radio station Rinse welcome a rare creature to their schedule for 4 Friday nights starting 9th October. Claptone is an otherworldly being who’s identity and character has been quite well hidden outside of the myriad events he has headlined. It’s odd that someone who performs in front of 100,000’s of fans a year can remain an enigma… but perhaps for not much longer.

We know he’s from Berlin and we love his soul moving body music, but his golden scooped beak and blacked out clothing hide a history that we are sure many of us want to explore. 
 
Rinse have invited many guests to host a series of 4 Friday evening shows over the past months but we’ve been told that Claptone has worked with the team to deliver something quite different. Expect a tale split across each episode that weaves in some biographical information in between some of the coolest house music and more. Claptone will be releasing his debut artist album on Different Recordings on 16th October and will be hosting a huge Masquerade Halloween party at Southwark St Warehouse in London on 31st October as part of his global album tour so this set of shows should pique the interest of anyone looking forward to this milestones in his career.
